</pre> <p>The bigger pattern. Every QC check is a research-time "I bet this won't break" turned into a permanent runtime guard. CI gets a pipeline-correctness suite for free, and pipelines self-document their preconditions.</p> In [20]: Copied! <pre>class Quarantine(Operator):
    """On check failure: log + return sentinel; on success: pass through."""

    forbid_in_yaml = True

    def __init__(self, check: Operator, *, sentinel, on_quarantine=None) -&gt; None:
        self.check = check
        self.sentinel = sentinel
        self.on_quarantine = on_quarantine or (lambda x, err: None)

    def _apply(self, x):
        try:
            self.check(x)
        except Exception as e:  # broad — Quarantine catches by design
            self.on_quarantine(x, e)
            return self.sentinel
        return x

    def get_config(self) -&gt; dict:
        return {"check": type(self.check).__name__}


